WEBVTT

00:11.633 --> 00:13.166
[TV static drones]

00:13.166 --> 00:15.233
[bright tone]

00:16.467 --> 00:19.467
[upbeat rock music]

00:19.467 --> 00:26.500
♪ ♪

00:36.100 --> 00:39.133
[cheers and applause]

00:42.734 --> 00:46.500
- Welcome, welcome, welcome
to "Last Week Tonight."

00:46.500 --> 00:49.900
I'm John Oliver, thank you
so, so much for joining us.

00:49.900 --> 00:53.233
We're back, and look,
a lot has happened--

00:53.233 --> 00:56.433
a lot has happened
since we last saw you,

00:56.433 --> 00:59.266
so--so we need to--
we need to address

00:59.266 --> 01:02.233
the big elephant in the room
straightaway.

01:02.233 --> 01:05.667
How about "The Young Pope,"
huh?

01:05.667 --> 01:07.433
Pretty crazy, right?

01:07.433 --> 01:10.433
There's a kangaroo
in the Vatican.

01:10.433 --> 01:12.633
I can't think of
anything more shocking

01:12.633 --> 01:14.934
to have happened
in the last few months.

01:14.934 --> 01:15.800
Oh, do you know what?

01:15.800 --> 01:18.266
I guess there was
that one thing.

01:18.266 --> 01:20.934
- And so now the United States
has a new president,

01:20.934 --> 01:23.100
the 45th president
of the United States.

01:23.100 --> 01:25.667
There he is, Donald J. Trump.

01:25.667 --> 01:26.867
- That's right.

01:26.867 --> 01:28.600
We now live
under President Trump.

01:28.600 --> 01:30.967
Two words that will never
sound normal together,

01:30.967 --> 01:32.800
no matter how many times
you say them,

01:32.800 --> 01:34.266
like "panda mustard"

01:34.266 --> 01:36.633
or "Mom's orgasm."

01:36.633 --> 01:38.867
Now, the last few weeks
have been frantic.

01:38.867 --> 01:40.800
Trump's nominated
a Supreme Court justice

01:40.800 --> 01:43.433
and issued 24 Executive orders
and memoranda.

01:43.433 --> 01:45.500
One of which,
the notorious travel ban

01:45.500 --> 01:47.367
has been smacked down
repeatedly in court.

01:47.367 --> 01:49.233
To which he tweeted
nonsensically,

01:49.233 --> 01:50.700
"SEE YOU IN COURT."

01:50.700 --> 01:52.600
He also somehow
failed to mention Jews

01:52.600 --> 01:54.133
in a Holocaust remembrance
statement,

01:54.133 --> 01:55.500
used the National
Prayer Breakfast

01:55.500 --> 01:57.300
to make fun of
Arnold Schwarzenegger's ratings

01:57.300 --> 01:58.467
on "The Celebrity Apprentice,"

01:58.467 --> 02:00.200
and Twitter-bullied
the Mexican president

02:00.200 --> 02:02.233
into cancelling his visit
to the U.S.

02:02.233 --> 02:04.834
And that is just the tip
of the shitberg.

02:04.834 --> 02:07.734
It has been so busy
it's gotten to the point

02:07.734 --> 02:10.433
where the most terrifying sound
is your phone buzzing

02:10.433 --> 02:11.867
with a news alert.

02:11.867 --> 02:14.600
I hate to say this,
but I actually found myself

02:14.600 --> 02:17.066
at one point saying,
"Oh, thank God.

02:17.066 --> 02:19.533
"It's just that
Mary Tyler Moore's dead.

02:19.533 --> 02:23.200
Oh, that is a massive relief."

02:23.200 --> 02:24.900
We've been living in a world

02:24.900 --> 02:27.166
where if someone says,
"Good morning" to you,

02:27.166 --> 02:29.500
the only acceptable response
is "No!

02:29.500 --> 02:32.567
No, it isn't!
What is wrong with you?"

02:32.567 --> 02:34.767
And even if you try
to avoid the news,

02:34.767 --> 02:36.767
inevitably, someone will
come up to you and say,

02:36.767 --> 02:37.900
"Hey, did you hear?

02:37.900 --> 02:39.166
"The new secretary of labor

02:39.166 --> 02:41.700
is a giant jar of wasps."

02:41.700 --> 02:42.834
Now, I'm kidding about that.

02:42.834 --> 02:45.133
The actual nominee
is Andrew Puzder,

02:45.133 --> 02:46.800
who has opposed
raising the minimum wage

02:46.800 --> 02:49.467
and who currently heads
Hardee's and Carl's Jr.,

02:49.467 --> 02:52.433
the chains famous
for tasteful ads like this.

02:52.433 --> 02:53.600
[rock music]

02:53.600 --> 02:55.433
- Introducing
the classic Patty Melt,

02:55.433 --> 02:57.734
with a spicy twist.

02:57.734 --> 02:59.567
- ♪ Like it all night ♪

02:59.567 --> 03:02.700
♪ ♪

03:02.700 --> 03:04.734
♪ I like it hot ♪

03:04.734 --> 03:06.834
- That is truly
the perfect ad

03:06.834 --> 03:08.900
to prepare you for
the actual interior

03:08.900 --> 03:11.900
of a Carl's Jr. restaurant,
which is undeniably

03:11.900 --> 03:14.233
so hot.

03:14.233 --> 03:16.266
But before you can be
horrified by Puzder,

03:16.266 --> 03:17.967
you remember Trump's
attorney general

03:17.967 --> 03:20.567
is Jeff Sessions, recently named
"Man of the Year"

03:20.567 --> 03:23.000
by "Wrong Side of History"
magazine.

03:23.000 --> 03:24.633
In fact, all Trump's nominees

03:24.633 --> 03:26.433
seemed to have been
chosen sarcastically.

03:26.433 --> 03:29.300
The secretary of education hates
our public education system.

03:29.300 --> 03:32.367
The nominee to head the EPA
hates the EPA.

03:32.367 --> 03:35.233
And the future secretary
of energy is this guy.

03:35.233 --> 03:38.233
[country music playing]

03:38.233 --> 03:41.200
[mariachi music playing]

03:41.200 --> 03:42.367
♪ ♪

03:42.367 --> 03:44.300
[country musical flourish]

03:44.300 --> 03:45.433
[cheers and applause]

03:45.433 --> 03:47.000
Cool.

03:47.000 --> 03:49.300
Now, Rick Perry once proposed

03:49.300 --> 03:51.734
eliminating the department
that he will soon head.

03:51.734 --> 03:54.066
Although, to be fair,
he later recanted, saying,

03:54.066 --> 03:56.400
"After being briefed on
so many of the vital functions

03:56.400 --> 03:57.667
"of the Department of Energy,

03:57.667 --> 04:00.700
I regret recommending
its elimination."

04:00.700 --> 04:02.767
I can only imagine
he thought it protected

04:02.767 --> 04:04.934
our reserves of
Monster Energy drinks.

04:04.934 --> 04:07.867
"Come on, y'all, you can't have
monsters gettin' energy.

04:07.867 --> 04:09.867
"Why we even giving 'em drinks?

04:09.867 --> 04:12.100
"This department
needs to be shut down!

04:12.100 --> 04:15.000
Cha cha cha!"

04:15.000 --> 04:18.533
With the pace of chaos
reigning down upon us,

04:18.533 --> 04:20.567
it is important to find
something to center yourself.

04:20.567 --> 04:22.533
Now, personally,
I have been using

04:22.533 --> 04:25.133
this framed photograph
of Eddie,

04:25.133 --> 04:27.367
the dog from the TV show
"Frasier."

04:27.367 --> 04:29.900
I-I look at this
whenever I want to feel better.

04:29.900 --> 04:30.800
And I'll tell you why.

04:30.800 --> 04:32.633
Because Eddie is
the perfect example

04:32.633 --> 04:34.734
of something that has
absolutely no idea

04:34.734 --> 04:36.867
what's going on
in the world right now.

04:36.867 --> 04:38.867
He's a dog, he's fictional,

04:38.867 --> 04:40.500
and he's almost certainly dead.

04:40.500 --> 04:43.266
And at various times
these past few weeks,

04:43.266 --> 04:44.934
I have been genuinely jealous

04:44.934 --> 04:47.500
of all three of those things.

04:47.500 --> 04:50.066
This is going to be
a long presidency,

04:50.066 --> 04:52.467
and perhaps nothing
encapsulated the way

04:52.467 --> 04:54.400
many of us feel right now
better than

04:54.400 --> 04:57.300
Japanese Prime Minister
Shinzo Abe.

04:57.300 --> 04:59.200
On Friday, he met
with our new president

04:59.200 --> 05:01.133
for what was a comically-long

05:01.133 --> 05:03.033
and marathon-like handshake.

05:03.033 --> 05:06.166
But just watch his expression
at the end.

05:06.166 --> 05:07.433
[laughter]

05:07.433 --> 05:10.967
I feel you.
I feel you.

05:10.967 --> 05:12.000
[laughter and cheers]

05:12.000 --> 05:13.100
That is the prime minister

05:13.100 --> 05:14.633
of a country known

05:14.633 --> 05:17.300
for awkwardly-long
formal displays of respect,

05:17.300 --> 05:18.633
and he even he is going,

05:18.633 --> 05:22.400
"Oh, fuck this shit."

05:22.400 --> 05:24.200
And now this.

05:24.200 --> 05:27.266
[trumpet fanfare]

05:29.867 --> 05:32.667
- Thank you.
Thank you very much.

05:32.667 --> 05:34.100
[rimshot]

05:34.100 --> 05:36.433
