06:02.533 --> 06:05.500
[tambourine continues]

06:05.500 --> 06:07.033
♪ ♪

06:07.033 --> 06:09.667
[cheers and applause]

06:09.667 --> 06:10.867
- Moving on.

06:10.867 --> 06:12.500
Now, our main story tonight

06:12.500 --> 06:14.100
is going to be
a little different.

06:14.100 --> 06:16.533
Normally, we like to focus
this part of the show

06:16.533 --> 06:18.500
on complex, depressing
policy issues,

06:18.500 --> 06:22.400
something fun, like
CO2 emissions from hearses

06:22.400 --> 06:25.533
or space poverty
or the proliferation

06:25.533 --> 06:27.100
of special-purpose
taxing districts,

06:27.100 --> 06:29.266
a topic so boring
you didn't even realize

06:29.266 --> 06:33.000
we literally already did
that exact story last year.

06:33.000 --> 06:35.000
And we want to keep
doing those kind of things,

06:35.000 --> 06:37.400
but unfortunately we can't
until we address

06:37.400 --> 06:41.200
something even bigger:
the concept of reality itself.

06:41.200 --> 06:43.533
And that is because of this guy.

06:43.533 --> 06:47.066
Now, since taking office,
around 412 years ago,

06:47.066 --> 06:49.734
Trump has made it clear that

06:49.734 --> 06:52.533
reality is not important to him.
Think about it.

06:52.533 --> 06:54.934
Uh, he's exaggerated the size
of his inauguration crowd.

06:54.934 --> 06:57.400
He said the election was
marred by mass voter fraud

06:57.400 --> 06:58.700
with no real proof of that.

06:58.700 --> 07:00.633
Uh, he also falsely claimed
that--uh--

07:00.633 --> 07:03.633
that compared to Muslims,
it was "almost impossible"

07:03.633 --> 07:05.600
for Christian refugees
from Syria

07:05.600 --> 07:06.767
to get into the U.S.

07:06.767 --> 07:09.033
He even lied about the weather

07:09.033 --> 07:10.834
during his inauguration.

07:10.834 --> 07:13.000
- It was--almost raining.

07:13.000 --> 07:14.433
The rain should have
scared them away,

07:14.433 --> 07:15.734
but God looked down
and He said,

07:15.734 --> 07:17.934
"We're not gonna
let it rain on your speech."

07:17.934 --> 07:20.000
- No, he didn't.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.900
First, it did rain
while you were speaking.

07:22.900 --> 07:25.433
That's why your wife was
holding up an umbrella

07:25.433 --> 07:28.567
and people behind you
were wearing ponchos.

07:28.567 --> 07:30.934
And second,
if God did look down

07:30.934 --> 07:32.033
his only thought
would have been,

07:32.033 --> 07:35.433
"Wait.
The Mormon Tabernacle Choir?

07:35.433 --> 07:37.967
"Come on, I'm sick of them,
and I'm God.

07:37.967 --> 07:39.567
"Could you not book silence,

07:39.567 --> 07:42.367
or was silence somehow
boycotting this thing too?"

07:42.367 --> 07:45.934
So--so that is where
we are currently at.

07:45.934 --> 07:48.800
We have a president
capable of standing in the rain

07:48.800 --> 07:50.767
and saying it was a sunny day.

07:50.767 --> 07:53.533
And before we go any further,
"Donald Trump lies"

07:53.533 --> 07:56.333
is clearly not
a fresh observation.

07:56.333 --> 07:58.066
Liberals are probably
thinking, "Wow.

07:58.066 --> 07:59.567
"Hot take there, Johnny.

07:59.567 --> 08:02.133
"Uh, next you're gonna tell me
that Obama is aloof;

08:02.133 --> 08:04.900
"Dick Cheney is evil;
and Paul Ryan doesn't climax

08:04.900 --> 08:07.033
"until he's checked his Fitbit
to see how many calories

08:07.033 --> 08:08.800
he's burned from fucking."

08:08.800 --> 08:10.567
And--and you know what?

08:10.567 --> 08:12.400
If you're on the other side,

08:12.400 --> 08:14.367
if you're on the right,
you're probably thinking,

08:14.367 --> 08:16.533
"Oh, great,
another blizzard of snowflakes

08:16.533 --> 08:19.734
from 'Last Cuck Tonight
with Johnny Trigger-Warning.'"

08:19.734 --> 08:21.266
And--and, yes,

08:21.266 --> 08:25.433
I know all other
presidents have lied.

08:25.433 --> 08:27.633
PolitiFact found that
just over 1/4

08:27.633 --> 08:30.033
of President Obama's statements
that they evaluated

08:30.033 --> 08:31.400
were some degree of false.

08:31.400 --> 08:33.133
But with Trump, that number

08:33.133 --> 08:35.400
is currently over 2/3.

08:35.400 --> 08:38.200
Perhaps that is why one reporter
who's been covering Trump

08:38.200 --> 08:40.367
found himself saying this.

08:40.367 --> 08:42.600
- This is what makes it--
covering Donald Trump

08:42.600 --> 08:44.266
so very difficult.

08:44.266 --> 08:46.700
What does he mean
when he says words?

08:46.700 --> 08:48.600
[laughter]

08:48.600 --> 08:50.633
- Wow.

08:50.633 --> 08:53.367
"What does he mean
when he says words?"

08:53.367 --> 08:55.967
We are talking about
the president

08:55.967 --> 08:59.433
like a Tinder match
we've been on four dates with.

08:59.433 --> 09:01.834
"Uh, I asked him if
we could hang out this Friday,

09:01.834 --> 09:05.300
"and he said,
'Prolly... I'm starving

09:05.300 --> 09:07.734
"bicycle emoji, poop emoji.'

09:07.734 --> 09:09.400
"What the fuck does that mean?

09:09.400 --> 09:12.700
What does he mean
when he says words?"

09:12.700 --> 09:14.600
Trump's relationship
with the truth

09:14.600 --> 09:17.400
is going to be of profound
importance going forward

09:17.400 --> 09:19.500
because any policy discussion

09:19.500 --> 09:22.500
has to begin with
a shared sense of reality.

09:22.500 --> 09:26.500
And Trump's reality can change
within a single sentence.

09:26.500 --> 09:30.567
- When you hear
4.9% and 5% unemployment,

09:30.567 --> 09:35.467
the number's probably
28%, 29%, as high as 35%--

09:35.467 --> 09:38.700
in fact, I even
heard recently 42%.

09:38.700 --> 09:42.533
- Well--well which one
is it then?

09:42.533 --> 09:45.066
Because a 4.9% rate
might result in

09:45.066 --> 09:47.333
a cautiously constrictive
monetary policy,

09:47.333 --> 09:49.633
whereas a 42% rate

09:49.633 --> 09:52.834
might result in "The Purge."

09:52.834 --> 09:55.367
So--so tonight,
we thought it would be useful

09:55.367 --> 09:57.533
to try and answer
four basic questions.

09:57.533 --> 10:00.400
How did we get a pathological
liar in the White House?

10:00.400 --> 10:02.266
Where are his lies
coming from?

10:02.266 --> 10:04.266
Why do so many people
believe him?

10:04.266 --> 10:06.266
And what can we
possibly do about it?

10:06.266 --> 10:07.767
And to that first question,

10:07.767 --> 10:10.300
Trump's lying is obviously
nothing new.

10:10.300 --> 10:14.166
He has a well-documented
40-year history of bullshit.

10:14.166 --> 10:16.600
Uh, he lied about
being invited on this show,

10:16.600 --> 10:19.200
uh, and about the ratings
for "The Celebrity Apprentice."

10:19.200 --> 10:21.200
He pretended to be
his own publicist.

10:21.200 --> 10:23.400
Even his building, Trump Tower,

10:23.400 --> 10:25.834
is not as big as
he says it is.

10:25.834 --> 10:27.734
- He inflated the floor numbers.

10:27.734 --> 10:32.200
His 58-story building
became a 68-story building.

10:32.200 --> 10:34.467
- It made a lot of sense
in his mind because

10:34.467 --> 10:36.567
if you're renting a room,
you'd rather be on

10:36.567 --> 10:38.700
the 14th floor
than on the 6th floor.

10:38.700 --> 10:40.800
- Just spare a thought

10:40.800 --> 10:44.567
for confused firefighters
turning up to that building.

10:44.567 --> 10:47.834
"The smoke alarm's going off in
penthouse B on the 68th floor,

10:47.834 --> 10:50.834
"which is apparently
an alcove studio on the 58th.

10:50.834 --> 10:54.133
Quick, it's an emergency!"

10:54.133 --> 10:56.900
But lies like that
are almost charming.

10:56.900 --> 10:59.133
What is less harmless
is when he started

10:59.133 --> 11:00.967
lying about the president's
birth certificate

11:00.967 --> 11:02.867
and then,
as a presidential candidate,

11:02.867 --> 11:05.900
started making troubling
statements like these.

11:05.900 --> 11:08.767
- The murder rate
in the United States,

11:08.767 --> 11:12.700
it's the worst, the highest
it's been in 45 years.

11:12.700 --> 11:16.333
Our president wants to
take in 250,000 from Syria.

11:16.333 --> 11:20.233
Our gross domestic product,

11:20.233 --> 11:22.700
a sign of strength, right?

11:22.700 --> 11:25.233
But not for us.

11:25.233 --> 11:28.967
It was below zero.
Who ever heard of this?

11:28.967 --> 11:31.000
- Okay, okay, just--just--

11:31.000 --> 11:32.800
just real quick on those.

11:32.800 --> 11:35.133
No, it isn't; no, he didn't;

11:35.133 --> 11:37.967
and no one's ever heard
of a GDP below zero

11:37.967 --> 11:40.900
because that is
fucking impossible!

11:40.900 --> 11:43.467
Now, any one of those falsehoods

11:43.467 --> 11:47.200
could have disqualified him
for office.

11:47.200 --> 11:49.800
But--but we were so accustomed
to Trump's nonsense,

11:49.800 --> 11:52.700
people could just shrug it off
as "Donald being Donald."

11:52.700 --> 11:55.166
Even his own advisers,
like Peter Thiel,

11:55.166 --> 11:57.800
argued that people shouldn't
worry about his statements

11:57.800 --> 11:59.934
because he didn't
really mean them.

11:59.934 --> 12:02.967
- I think a lot of the voters
who vote for Trump,

12:02.967 --> 12:06.266
um, take Trump seriously
but not literally.

12:06.266 --> 12:08.567
And so when
they hear things like,

12:08.567 --> 12:10.700
the Muslim comment
or the wall comment

12:10.700 --> 12:12.867
or things like that,
it's not, uh,

12:12.867 --> 12:14.767
the question's not, you know,
"Are you gonna build a wall

12:14.767 --> 12:16.533
like the Great Wall of China?"

12:16.533 --> 12:18.200
Or, you know, "How--how exactly

12:18.200 --> 12:20.000
are you gonna enforce
these--these tests?"

12:20.000 --> 12:23.266
What they hear is, uh,
"We're gonna have--

12:23.266 --> 12:26.967
we're gonna have a saner, more
sensible immigration policy."

12:26.967 --> 12:30.166
- Oh, yeah, that is
definitely the sense I got

12:30.166 --> 12:31.900
from watching
those Trump rallies.

12:31.900 --> 12:35.500
"Yes, while we're all furiously
chanting 'Build that wall,'

12:35.500 --> 12:37.467
"we all understand
in this context

12:37.467 --> 12:40.133
"'wall' is a clever use
of metonymy,

12:40.133 --> 12:42.867
"uh, or a figure of speech
in which one word,

12:42.867 --> 12:45.667
"'wall' in this example,
is used as a stand-in

12:45.667 --> 12:48.734
"for 'a saner, more sensible
immigration policy.'

12:48.734 --> 12:50.200
"Now, if you will,

12:50.200 --> 12:54.133
let's unpack
'Trump the bitch.'"

12:54.133 --> 12:56.133
And--and yet,

12:56.133 --> 12:58.567
the travel ban
literally happened.

12:58.567 --> 13:00.266
And as for the wall...

13:00.266 --> 13:04.600
- The wall is getting
designed right now.

13:04.600 --> 13:06.967
A lot of people say,
"Oh, oh.

13:06.967 --> 13:08.600
Trump was only kidding
with the wall."

13:08.600 --> 13:09.934
I wasn't kidd--I don't kid.

13:09.934 --> 13:11.266
- Exactly.

13:11.266 --> 13:13.300
When he says
he's going to build a wall,

13:13.300 --> 13:14.433
