13:16.033 --> 13:18.367
and labeled "156 stories,"

13:18.367 --> 13:20.567
but assume that it's coming.

13:20.567 --> 13:23.000
So it was worth
taking him seriously.

13:23.000 --> 13:26.066
Trump was telling the truth
about his solutions

13:26.066 --> 13:28.100
to the problems
he was lying about.

13:28.100 --> 13:30.700
And he is now
making real policy

13:30.700 --> 13:32.166
based on fake facts.

13:32.166 --> 13:34.266
Which brings us
to our second question,

13:34.266 --> 13:36.667
where is his
information coming from?

13:36.667 --> 13:40.000
Now, Trump himself has admitted
he gets a lot of it from TV.

13:40.000 --> 13:42.667
Which may explain why
he speaks so confidently about

13:42.667 --> 13:45.200
cable news staples
like crime and terrorism,

13:45.200 --> 13:47.834
but when it comes to
the nuts-and-bolts aspects

13:47.834 --> 13:50.700
of government, like the
nuclear triad, he struggles.

13:50.700 --> 13:53.500
Now, he famously flubbed
a question on the triad during

13:53.500 --> 13:56.967
an early debate in an exchange
that ended like this.

13:56.967 --> 13:58.700
- Of the three legs
of the triad, though,

13:58.700 --> 14:00.200
do you have a priority?

14:00.200 --> 14:01.533
'Cause I want to go to Senator
Rubio after that and ask him--

14:01.533 --> 14:03.533
