16:25.734 --> 16:27.166
And why are you in a library,

16:27.166 --> 16:30.633
and one that doesn't want
to overdo it with the books?

16:30.633 --> 16:33.767
You fascinate me.

16:33.767 --> 16:36.734
But Trump doesn't
just watch cable news.

16:36.734 --> 16:38.233
He also takes information in

16:38.233 --> 16:40.567
from frighteningly unreliable
sources,

16:40.567 --> 16:42.900
such as Breitbart,
the organization

16:42.900 --> 16:44.333
which gave us Steve Bannon...
[crowd booing]

16:44.333 --> 16:47.467
Steve Bannon, now
Trump's chief strategist.

16:47.467 --> 16:51.000
Breitbart has published
such Pulitzer-eligible stories

16:51.000 --> 16:54.700
as "Birth Control Makes Women
Unattractive and Crazy,"

16:54.700 --> 16:57.834
"Racist, Pro-Nazi Roots
of Planned Parenthood Revealed,"

16:57.834 --> 16:59.600
and "Hoist It High and Proud:

16:59.600 --> 17:02.100
The Confederate Flag
Proclaims a Glorious Heritage."

17:02.100 --> 17:04.166
You know, the kind of--
the kind of headlines

17:04.166 --> 17:05.734
you see your old
high school friend

17:05.734 --> 17:08.467
share on Facebook and think,
"Oh, that's a shame.

17:08.467 --> 17:11.367
I guess Greg sucks now."

17:11.367 --> 17:13.700
But--but Trump's
trust in Breitbart

17:13.700 --> 17:15.333
actually goes way back.

17:15.333 --> 17:18.066
A few years ago, Trump was
challenged by Bill O'Reilly,

17:18.066 --> 17:20.400
who correctly pointed out
that his claim

17:20.400 --> 17:23.066
that thousands of Muslims
were seen celebrating

17:23.066 --> 17:26.767
in New Jersey on 9/11 was
based on no evidence whatsoever.

17:26.767 --> 17:29.133
And this is how Trump responded.

17:29.133 --> 17:30.700
- Well, I don't know
that I'm wrong, Bill.

17:30.700 --> 17:33.133
You know, uh, this just
came out from Breitbart.

17:33.133 --> 17:35.266
I mean, literally,
it just came out.

17:35.266 --> 17:37.967
"Trump Vindicated--
100% Vindicated."

17:37.967 --> 17:39.333
- Believe me, if there
were thousands,

17:39.333 --> 17:40.667
that would have been reported.

17:40.667 --> 17:42.066
Um, but--but what I'm trying
to get at is this--

17:42.066 --> 17:43.467
- Well, this article says
they were swarming.

17:43.467 --> 17:45.467
Bill, this article
says they were

17:45.467 --> 17:46.967
swarming all over the place.
- All right.

17:46.967 --> 17:48.300
- So I don't know
what that means,

17:48.300 --> 17:49.600
but it means a lot of people.

17:49.600 --> 17:51.266
- Wait.

17:51.266 --> 17:53.333
Holding up a Breitbart article

17:53.333 --> 17:55.767
does not make you seem
more credible.

17:55.767 --> 17:58.266
You might as well have gone,
"Oh, hold on a second, Bill.

17:58.266 --> 18:00.200
"Hello?
Okay, thanks.

18:00.200 --> 18:02.233
"Sources are saying
I'm right, Bill.

18:02.233 --> 18:04.266
"My sources--talk to them.

18:04.266 --> 18:06.500
Talk to my sources, William."

18:06.500 --> 18:07.500
[cheers and applause]

18:07.500 --> 18:09.934
And--and Trump's sources

18:09.934 --> 18:12.000
get even worse,
because he also cited

18:12.000 --> 18:14.400
an article to support his
"Muslims on 9/11" claim

18:14.400 --> 18:18.100
from Infowars,
a website run by this guy.

18:18.100 --> 18:22.100
- Hillary and Obama want to
make you poor and pathetic.

18:22.100 --> 18:24.767
We have all their white papers.
They hate you!

18:24.767 --> 18:27.567
They hate prosperity!
They hate God!

18:27.567 --> 18:30.600
They hate children!
And God damn them to Hell!

18:30.600 --> 18:33.700
- That man--
that man is Alex Jones.

18:33.700 --> 18:36.900
And that is actually
him at his most presentable.

18:36.900 --> 18:39.633
That is Alex Jones
at a job interview.

18:39.633 --> 18:42.166
That's Alex Jones meeting
his girlfriend's parents

18:42.166 --> 18:43.867
for the first time.

18:43.867 --> 18:45.767
Now, in his
more outspoken moments,

18:45.767 --> 18:48.133
Jones has argued that
the government has the ability

18:48.133 --> 18:49.567
to control tornados;

18:49.567 --> 18:52.200
that the Boston Marathon bombing
was a false-flag attack;

18:52.200 --> 18:54.567
and that tap water
is a gay bomb;

18:54.567 --> 18:56.867
and that they are
putting chemicals in the water

18:56.867 --> 18:59.533
that turn
the friggin' frogs gay.

18:59.533 --> 19:02.800
And then, there is
the Sandy Hook school shooting.

19:02.800 --> 19:04.967
- Yeah, so, Sandy Hook

19:04.967 --> 19:09.567
is a synthetic,
completely fake, with actors,

19:09.567 --> 19:11.467
in my view, manufactured.

19:11.467 --> 19:13.233
I couldn't believe it at first.

19:13.233 --> 19:15.233
I knew they had
actors there, clearly,

19:15.233 --> 19:17.033
but I thought
they killed some real kids.

19:17.033 --> 19:20.033
And it just shows
how bold they are,

19:20.033 --> 19:22.667
that they clearly used actors.

19:22.667 --> 19:25.333
- Now,
that is not just offensive,

19:25.333 --> 19:26.500
it's stupid.

19:26.500 --> 19:29.633
If the government had
actually hired child actors,

19:29.633 --> 19:31.633
there is no way
their stage parents

19:31.633 --> 19:33.367
would have stopped
talking about it.

19:33.367 --> 19:35.333
"Well, he didn't
get the Tide commercial,

19:35.333 --> 19:37.767
"but he did book a leading role
in a government-sponsored

19:37.767 --> 19:39.066
"false-flag attack.

19:39.066 --> 19:41.533
"It's the same director
who did the moon landing.

19:41.533 --> 19:44.500
We're very excited."

19:44.500 --> 19:46.967
Trump is apparently
such a fan

19:46.967 --> 19:48.867
that Alex Jones himself
has said,

19:48.867 --> 19:51.600
"It is surreal
to talk about issues here on air

19:51.600 --> 19:54.700
and then word for word hear
Trump say it two days later."

19:54.700 --> 19:56.400
And I would be skeptical of that

19:56.400 --> 19:59.266
if Trump hadn't
gone on Jones's show

19:59.266 --> 20:00.567
and said this.

20:00.567 --> 20:01.934
- I just want
to finish by saying

20:01.934 --> 20:03.567
your reputation's amazing.

20:03.567 --> 20:05.367
I will not let you down.

20:05.367 --> 20:08.567
You will be very, very,
uh, impressed, I hope.

20:08.567 --> 20:10.467
And I think we'll be
speaking a lot.

20:10.467 --> 20:11.600
- You know what?

20:11.600 --> 20:13.467
I-I guess it makes sense
that Donald Trump

20:13.467 --> 20:15.100
wants to impress Alex Jones.

20:15.100 --> 20:16.734
Why would you want
to drain the swamp

20:16.734 --> 20:19.667
if not to eradicate
all those gay frogs?

20:19.667 --> 20:23.500
You stay there.
You two stay where you are.

20:23.500 --> 20:26.000
This is really dangerous,
though.

20:26.000 --> 20:27.500
Because there is a pattern here.

20:27.500 --> 20:30.133
Trump sees something
that jibes with his world view,

20:30.133 --> 20:32.400
doesn't check it,
half-remembers it,

20:32.400 --> 20:33.900
and then passes it on.

20:33.900 --> 20:36.300
At which point, it takes on
a life of its own,

20:36.300 --> 20:37.867
and appears to validate itself.

20:37.867 --> 20:40.633
Let me try and show you
that machine in action.

20:40.633 --> 20:42.333
Trump's constant claim that

20:42.333 --> 20:44.133
millions of people
voted illegally

20:44.133 --> 20:46.133
originated,
as far as anyone can tell,

20:46.133 --> 20:49.300
from some dude on Twitter
who claimed in November,

20:49.300 --> 20:52.166
while providing no evidence,
"We have verified

20:52.166 --> 20:55.367
more than three million votes
cast by non-citizens."

20:55.367 --> 20:57.934
The next day,
Infowars picked that up,

20:57.934 --> 21:00.800
and it spread like jet fuel
among the right-wing sites.

21:00.800 --> 21:03.333
Now, it was quickly debunked
by multiple outlets,

21:03.333 --> 21:05.767
but despite that,
days later,

21:05.767 --> 21:08.333
President-elect Trump
started tweeting

21:08.333 --> 21:10.633
about millions of illegal votes

21:10.633 --> 21:13.433
and serious voter fraud
in states like California.

21:13.433 --> 21:16.200
And by early December,
people were on TV,

21:16.200 --> 21:18.567
expressing similar concerns.

21:18.567 --> 21:21.033
- Voting is a privilege
in this country.

21:21.033 --> 21:24.200
And you need to be legal,
not like California,

21:24.200 --> 21:26.233
where 3 million illegals voted.

21:26.233 --> 21:28.166
- Where are you
getting your information?

21:28.166 --> 21:29.333
- From the media.

21:29.333 --> 21:31.867
- And that right there
actually answers

21:31.867 --> 21:34.700
our third question of why
so many people believe Trump.

21:34.700 --> 21:38.133
Because if you get your news
from similar sources to him

21:38.133 --> 21:40.533
as many, many, many people do,

21:40.533 --> 21:42.633
he doesn't look like a crank.

21:42.633 --> 21:44.166
He looks like
the first president

21:44.166 --> 21:46.000
ever to tell you the real truth.

21:46.000 --> 21:49.600
But rumors can be really
tenacious, and I'll prove it.

21:49.600 --> 21:51.300
What rumor do you think of

21:51.300 --> 21:54.233
when you hear the name
Richard Gere?

21:54.233 --> 21:55.734
Well, here's the thing.

21:55.734 --> 21:58.367
There is no proof
that he did that.

21:58.367 --> 22:00.433
If you think about it,
it's ridiculous.

22:00.433 --> 22:02.700
Have you ever held
one of those things?

22:02.700 --> 22:05.333
There's no way it was possible.

22:05.333 --> 22:07.367
But if the president
went on TV

22:07.367 --> 22:09.734
and told you it was true,
you'd go, "I knew it.

22:09.734 --> 22:11.767
"Thank you!
I knew it.

22:11.767 --> 22:13.834
Finally, someone said it."

22:13.834 --> 22:15.800
But that loop
gets much more dangerous

22:15.800 --> 22:17.000
when you're not talking about

22:17.000 --> 22:19.500
something as silly as gerbils.

22:19.500 --> 22:23.100
Trump validated his supporters'
beliefs about voter fraud,

22:23.100 --> 22:25.667
and in turn, they validated his.

22:25.667 --> 22:27.800
Because even when he was
directly confronted

22:27.800 --> 22:30.600
with the lack of evidence,
this is how he responded.

22:30.600 --> 22:31.834
- You know what's important?

22:31.834 --> 22:34.734
Millions of people agree with me
when I say that.

22:34.734 --> 22:36.900
If you would have looked
on one of the other networks

22:36.900 --> 22:38.900
and all of the people
that were calling in,

22:38.900 --> 22:40.734
they're saying,
"We agree with Mr. Trump.

22:40.734 --> 22:42.133
We agree."
They're very smart people.

22:42.133 --> 22:44.967
- Right, but just because
they believe you

22:44.967 --> 22:47.867
and you believe them,
doesn't make it true.

22:47.867 --> 22:51.100
This isn't like "Peter Pan,"
where believing in fairies

22:51.100 --> 22:53.066
will keep Tinker Bell alive.

22:53.066 --> 22:55.066
This isn't a magic thing,
Peter,

22:55.066 --> 22:57.934
she has Lou Gehrig's disease.

22:57.934 --> 22:59.767
And maybe instead of clapping,
you should have done

22:59.767 --> 23:02.867
the Ice Bucket Challenge,
then she'd still be alive!

23:02.867 --> 23:05.500
I'm sorry, Peter,
but she's dying!

23:05.500 --> 23:09.633
Tinker Bell's dying!

23:09.633 --> 23:11.800
The point is, even if

23:11.800 --> 23:14.266
you take the kindest
approach here,

23:14.266 --> 23:16.734
and assume Trump made
an honest, innocent mistake

23:16.734 --> 23:19.133
and passed along a news story
without checking it,

23:19.133 --> 23:21.667
when he was presented
with a lack of evidence,

23:21.667 --> 23:23.266
he disregarded that fact.

23:23.266 --> 23:25.967
At which point, he is lying.

23:25.967 --> 23:28.066
And it seems no one
in the White House

23:28.066 --> 23:29.233
has a problem with that.

23:29.233 --> 23:31.700
'Cause when asked to
justify the president's views,

23:31.700 --> 23:33.767
this is what Sean Spicer did.

23:33.767 --> 23:35.767
- I think the president
has believed that for a while.

23:35.767 --> 23:37.834
A long-standing belief
that he's maintained.

23:37.834 --> 23:38.967
It's a belief he maintains.

23:38.967 --> 23:41.000
It's a belief that
he's maintained for a while.

23:41.000 --> 23:42.767
As I noted several times now,

23:42.767 --> 23:44.233
he's believed this
for a long time.

23:44.233 --> 23:46.767
It was a comment that he made
on a long-standing belief.

23:46.767 --> 23:48.467
I've asked and answered
this question twice.

23:48.467 --> 23:49.500
He believes what he believes,

23:49.500 --> 23:50.867
based on the information
that he's provided.

23:50.867 --> 23:52.767
- If he does believe that, what
does that mean for democracy?

23:52.767 --> 23:54.700
- It means that, yeah,
I've answered your question.

23:54.700 --> 23:55.734
- Have you?

23:55.734 --> 23:59.133
- No, you haven't, Melissa.
No, you haven't.

23:59.133 --> 24:00.266
[laughter, cheers, and applause]

24:00.266 --> 24:04.033
Because this isn't
about belief.

24:04.033 --> 24:05.200
It can't be.

24:05.200 --> 24:09.100
The incidence of voter fraud
is a verifiable fact.

24:09.100 --> 24:10.934
And faith and fact

24:10.934 --> 24:13.133
aren't like
Bill Pullman and Bill Paxton.

24:13.133 --> 24:16.867
When you confuse them,
it actually matters.

24:16.867 --> 24:19.734
Real people get hurt
when you make policy

24:19.734 --> 24:20.867
based on false information.

24:20.867 --> 24:23.734
Billions will get spent
on a war that won't work,

24:23.734 --> 24:26.100
to prevent a crime wave
that isn't happening,

24:26.100 --> 24:28.400
while refugees
sit in dangerous situations

24:28.400 --> 24:30.433
to prevent
"Bowling Green" style massacres

24:30.433 --> 24:32.000
that never took place.

24:32.000 --> 24:35.033
So what are we going to do?

24:35.033 --> 24:38.333
Well, the press is
going to be a key element

24:38.333 --> 24:40.467
in helping us sort out
fact from fiction.

24:40.467 --> 24:42.266
And they are under attack.

24:42.266 --> 24:44.767
This administration has
seized on small corrections

24:44.767 --> 24:46.834
in news coverage
to paint critical outlets

24:46.834 --> 24:50.467
as fake news, attempting to
delegitimize all of them.

24:50.467 --> 24:52.500
And this is only
going to get worse.

24:52.500 --> 24:54.934
Steve Bannon has already
labeled the media

24:54.934 --> 24:56.300
"the opposition party."

24:56.300 --> 24:59.400
Although, there does
seem to be one exception.

24:59.400 --> 25:01.266
- News reports
said the only seat

25:01.266 --> 25:02.734
that was reserved for the media

25:02.734 --> 25:05.734
at Trump's news conference
Wednesday was in the front row,

25:05.734 --> 25:08.300
and it was for Breitbart News.

25:08.300 --> 25:11.400
- Oh, that is
some blatant favoritism!

25:11.400 --> 25:14.400
You are Snow White
introducing the dwarfs, saying,

25:14.400 --> 25:16.467
"Meet Grump, Sneezy, Sleepy,

25:16.467 --> 25:18.400
"Fucking-Awesome-Big-Dick-Cool
Dwarf,

25:18.400 --> 25:20.300
and the three others."

25:20.300 --> 25:21.734
And--and if you are thinking

25:21.734 --> 25:23.700
that Breitbart
went out of their way

25:23.700 --> 25:27.000
to ask a challenging question,
think again.

